Synopsis: Retrieves vector stores from the specified base URL.
Description: The Get-OAIVectorStore function retrieves vector stores from the specified base URL. It supports various parameters such as limit, order, after, before, and raw output.
Outputs: The function returns an array of vector stores or the raw response object, depending on the value of the Raw parameter.

Examples.Title: EXAMPLE 1
Examples.Code:
Get-OAIVectorStore -limit 10 -order desc
Retrieves the 10 most recent vector stores in descending order.
